    51function encode (obj, indent) {
    60 var deep = arguments[2]
    70 if (!indent) indent = " "
    8
    90 if (obj instanceof String ||
    10 Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === "[object String]") {
    110 obj = obj.toString()
    12 }
    13
    140 if (obj instanceof Number ||
    15 Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === "[object Number]") {
    160 obj = obj.valueOf()
    17 }
    18
    19 // take out the easy ones.
    200 switch (typeof obj) {
    21 case "string":
    220 obj = obj.trim()
    230 if (obj.indexOf("\n") !== -1) {
    240 return "|\n" + indent + obj.split(/\r?\n/).join("\n"+indent)
    25 } else {
    260 return (obj)
    27 }
    28
    29 case "number":
    300 return obj.toString(10)
    31
    32 case "function":
    330 return encode(obj.toString(), indent, true)
    34
    35 case "boolean":
    360 return obj.toString()
    37
    38 case "undefined":
    39 // fallthrough
    40 case "object":
    41 // at this point we know it types as an object
    420 if (!obj) return "~"
    43
    440 if (obj instanceof Date ||
    45 Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === "[object Date]") {
    460 return JSON.stringify("[Date " + obj.toISOString() + "]")
    47 }
    48
    490 if (obj instanceof RegExp ||
    50 Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === "[object RegExp]") {
    510 return JSON.stringify(obj.toString())
    52 }
    53
    540 if (obj instanceof Boolean ||
    55 Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === "[object Boolean]") {
    560 return obj.toString()
    57 }
    58
    590 if (seen.indexOf(obj) !== -1) {
    600 return "[Circular]"
    61 }
    620 seen.push(obj)
    63
    640 if (typeof Buffer === "function" &&
    65 typeof Buffer.isBuffer === "function" &&
    660 Buffer.isBuffer(obj)) return obj.inspect()
    67
    680 if (obj instanceof Error) {
    690 var o = { name: obj.name
    70 , message: obj.message
    71 , type: obj.type }

    730 if (obj.code) o.code = obj.code
    740 if (obj.errno) o.errno = obj.errno
    750 if (obj.type) o.type = obj.type
    760 obj = o
    77 }
    78
    790 var out = ""
    80
    810 if (Array.isArray(obj)) {
    820 var out = "\n" + indent + "- " +obj.map(function (item) {
    830 return encode(item, indent + " ", true)
    84 }).join("\n"+indent + "- ")
    850 break
    86 }
    87
    88 // an actual object
    890 var keys = Object.keys(obj)
    90 , niceKeys = keys.map(function (k) {
    910 return (k.match(/^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$/) ? k : JSON.stringify(k)) + ": "
    92 })

    950 return k.length

    100
    1010 if (!deep) indent += " "
    1020 out = "\n" + indent + keys.map(function (k, i) {
    1030 var niceKey = niceKeys[i]
    1040 return niceKey + spaces.substr(niceKey.length)
    105 + encode(obj[k], indent + " ", true)
    106 }).join("\n" + indent)
    1070 break
    108
    1090 default: return ""
    110 }
    1110 if (!deep) seen.length = 0

    1151function decode (str) {
    1160 var v = str.trim()
    117 , d
    118 , dateRe = /^\[Date ([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}T[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}(?::[0-9]{2})?(?:\.[0-9]{3})?(?:[A-Z]+)?)\]$/
    119
    1200 if (v === "~") return null
    121
    1220 try {
    1230 var jp = JSON.parse(str)
    124 } catch (e) {
    1250 var jp = ""
    126 }
    127
    1280 if (jp &&
    129 typeof jp === "string" &&
    130 (d = jp.match(dateRe)) &&
    131 (d = Date.parse(d[1]))) {
    1320 return new Date(d)
    133 }
    134
    1350 if (typeof jp === "boolean") return jp
    1360 if (v && !isNaN(v)) return parseInt(v, 10)
    137
    138 // something interesting.
    1390 var lines = str.split(/\r?\n/)
    140 // check if it's some kind of string or something.
    141 // if the first line is > or | then it's a wrapping indented string.
    142 // if the first line is blank, and there are many lines,
    143 // then it's an array or object.
    144 // otherwise, it's just ""
    1450 var first = lines.shift().trim()
    1460 if (lines.length) lines = undent(lines)
    1470 switch (first) {
    148 case "|":
    1490 return lines.join("\n")
    150 case ">":
    1510 return lines.join("\n").split(/\n{2,}/).map(function (l) {
    1520 return l.split(/\n/).join(" ")
    153 }).join("\n")
    154 default:
    1550 if (!lines.length) return first
    156 // array or object.
    157 // the first line will be either "- value" or "key: value"
    1580 return lines[0].charAt(0) === "-" ? decodeArr(lines) : decodeObj(lines)
    159 }
    160}
    161
    1621function decodeArr (lines) {
    1630 var out = []
    164 , key = 0
    165 , val = []
    1660 for (var i = 0, l = lines.length; i < l; i ++) {
    167 // if it starts with a -, then it's a new thing
    1680 var line = lines[i]
    1690 if (line.charAt(0) === "-") {
    1700 if (val.length) {
    1710 out[key ++] = decode(val.join("\n"))
    1720 val.length = 0
    173 }
    1740 val.push(line.substr(1).trim())
    1750 } else if (line.charAt(0) === " ") {
    1760 val.push(line)
    1770 } else return []
    178 }
    1790 if (val.length) {

    811TapConsumer.prototype.end = function () {

    1011TapConsumer.prototype._parseLine = function (line) {
    1020 if (this.bailedOut) return
    103 //console.error("_parseLine", [line])

    1120 if (this._current.ok) this._passed.push(this._current.id)

    127 }

    1380 var start = +(plan[1])
    139 , end = +(plan[2])

    1470 if (this._actualCount !== 0) {
    1480 this._sawPlan = true

    1500 return

    1540 this._parseResultLine(line)

    1721TapConsumer.prototype._parseResultLine = function (line) {

    4071Runner.prototype.mergeCovStats = function(cb) {
    4080 var self = this
    4090 self.rawCovStats.forEach(function(st) {
    4100 Object.keys(st).forEach(function(i) {

    421 function(l) {
    4220 return (st[i].lines.indexOf(l))

    430 // which is using array indexes for line numbers instead of the right number
    4310 Object.keys(self.covStats).forEach(function(f) {
    4320 self.covStats[f].missing = self.covStats[f].missing.map(function(line) {
    4330 return { number: line.number, source: line.source }

    4380 if (!self.covStats[f]) {
    4390 self.covStats[f] = { missing: self.coverageFilesSource[f]
    440 , percentage: 0

    4460 if (!self.covStats[f].percentage) {
    4470 self.covStats[f].percentage =
    448 1 - (self.covStats[f].missing.length / self.covStats[f].loc)

    141function asyncMap () {
    150 var steps = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments)
    16 , list = steps.shift() || []
    17 , cb_ = steps.pop()
    180 if (typeof cb_ !== "function") throw new Error(
    19 "No callback provided to asyncMap")
    200 if (!list) return cb_(null, [])
    210 if (!Array.isArray(list)) list = [list]
    220 var n = steps.length
    23 , data = [] // 2d array
    24 , errState = null
    25 , l = list.length
    26 , a = l * n
    270 if (!a) return cb_(null, [])
    280 function cb (er) {
    290 if (errState) return
    300 var argLen = arguments.length
    310 for (var i = 1; i < argLen; i ++) if (arguments[i] !== undefined) {
    320 data[i - 1] = (data[i - 1] || []).concat(arguments[i])
    33 }
    34 // see if any new things have been added.
    350 if (list.length > l) {
    360 var newList = list.slice(l)
    370 a += (list.length - l) * n
    380 l = list.length
    390 process.nextTick(function () {
    400 newList.forEach(function (ar) {
    410 steps.forEach(function (fn) { fn(ar, cb) })
    42 })
    43 })
    44 }
    45
    460 if (er || --a === 0) {
    470 errState = er
    480 cb_.apply(null, [errState].concat(data))
    49 }
    50 }
    51 // expect the supplied cb function to be called
    52 // "n" times for each thing in the array.
    530 list.forEach(function (ar) {
    540 steps.forEach(function (fn) { fn(ar, cb) })
    55 })
    56}

    12//following http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-selectors/#nth-child-pseudo
    13
    14//[ ['-'|'+']? INTEGER? {N} [ S* ['-'|'+'] S* INTEGER ]?
    151var re_nthElement = /^([+\-]?\d*n)?\s*(?:([+\-]?)\s*(\d+))?$/;
    16
    17/*
    18 parses a nth-check formula, returns an array of two numbers
    19*/
    201function parse(formula){
    210 formula = formula.trim().toLowerCase();
    22
    230 if(formula === "even"){
    240 return [2, 0];
    250 } else if(formula === "odd"){
    260 return [2, 1];
    27 } else {
    280 var parsed = formula.match(re_nthElement);
    29
    300 if(!parsed){
    310 throw new SyntaxError("n-th rule couldn't be parsed ('" + formula + "')");
    32 }
    33
    340 var a;
    35
    360 if(parsed[1]){
    370 a = parseInt(parsed[1], 10);
    380 if(!a){
    390 if(parsed[1].charAt(0) === "-") a = -1;
    400 else a = 1;
    41 }
    420 } else a = 0;
    43
    440 return [
    45 a,
    46 parsed[3] ? parseInt((parsed[2] || "") + parsed[3], 10) : 0
    47 ];
    48 }
    49}
    50
    51/*
    52 returns a function that checks if an elements index matches the given rule
    53 highly optimized to return the fastest solution
    54*/
    551function compile(parsed){
    560 var a = parsed[0],
    57 b = parsed[1] - 1;
    58
    59 //when b <= 0, a*n won't be possible for any matches when a < 0
    60 //besides, the specification says that no element is matched when a and b are 0
    610 if(b < 0 && a <= 0) return falseFunc;
    62
    63 //when a is in the range -1..1, it matches any element (so only b is checked)
    640 if(a ===-1) return function(pos){ return pos <= b; };
    650 if(a === 0) return function(pos){ return pos === b; };
    66 //when b <= 0 and a === 1, they match any element
    670 if(a === 1) return b < 0 ? trueFunc : function(pos){ return pos >= b; };
    68
    69 //when a > 0, modulo can be used to check if there is a match
    700 var bMod = b % a;
    710 if(bMod < 0) bMod += a;
    72
    730 if(a > 1){
    740 return function(pos){
    750 return pos >= b && pos % a === bMod;
    76 };
    77 }
    78
    790 a *= -1; //make `a` positive
    80
    810 return function(pos){
    820 return pos <= b && pos % a === bMod;
    83 };
    84}

    41//unescape function taken from https://github.com/jquery/sizzle/blob/master/src/sizzle.js#L139
    421function funescape( _, escaped, escapedWhitespace ) {
    430 var high = "0x" + escaped - 0x10000;
    44 // NaN means non-codepoint
    45 // Support: Firefox
    46 // Workaround erroneous numeric interpretation of +"0x"
    470 return high !== high || escapedWhitespace ?
    48 escaped :
    49 // BMP codepoint
    50 high < 0 ?
    51 String.fromCharCode( high + 0x10000 ) :
    52 // Supplemental Plane codepoint (surrogate pair)
    53 String.fromCharCode( high >> 10 | 0xD800, high & 0x3FF | 0xDC00 );
    54}

    353 // Use a comparator function to figure out the smallest index at which
    354 // an object should be inserted so as to maintain order. Uses binary search.

    3560 iterator = iterator == null ? _.identity : lookupIterator(iterator);
    3570 var value = iterator.call(context, obj);
    3580 var low = 0, high = array.length;
    3590 while (low < high) {
    3600 var mid = (low + high) >>> 1;
    3610 iterator.call(context, array[mid]) < value ? low = mid + 1 : high = mid;
    362 }
    3630 return low;

    518 // If the browser doesn't supply us with indexOf (I'm looking at you, **MSIE**),
    519 // we need this function. Return the position of the first occurrence of an
    520 // item in an array, or -1 if the item is not included in the array.
    521 // Delegates to **ECMAScript 5**'s native `indexOf` if available.
    522 // If the array is large and already in sort order, pass `true`
    523 // for **isSorted** to use binary search.
    5241 _.indexOf = function(array, item, isSorted) {
    5250 if (array == null) return -1;
    5260 var i = 0, l = array.length;
    5270 if (isSorted) {
    5280 if (typeof isSorted == 'number') {
    5290 i = (isSorted < 0 ? Math.max(0, l + isSorted) : isSorted);
    530 } else {
    5310 i = _.sortedIndex(array, item);
    5320 return array[i] === item ? i : -1;
    533 }
    534 }
    5350 if (nativeIndexOf && array.indexOf === nativeIndexOf) return array.indexOf(item, isSorted);
    5360 for (; i < l; i++) if (array[i] === item) return i;
    5370 return -1;
    538 };

    552 // Generate an integer Array containing an arithmetic progression. A port of
    553 // the native Python `range()` function. See
    554 // [the Python documentation](http://docs.python.org/library/functions.html#range).
    5551 _.range = function(start, stop, step) {
    5560 if (arguments.length <= 1) {
    5570 stop = start || 0;
    5580 start = 0;
    559 }
    5600 step = arguments[2] || 1;
    561
    5620 var len = Math.max(Math.ceil((stop - start) / step), 0);
    5630 var idx = 0;
    5640 var range = new Array(len);
    565
    5660 while(idx < len) {
    5670 range[idx++] = start;
    5680 start += step;
    569 }
    570
    5710 return range;
    572 };

    629 // Returns a function, that, when invoked, will only be triggered at most once
    630 // during a given window of time.
    6311 _.throttle = function(func, wait) {
    6320 var context, args, timeout, result;
    6330 var previous = 0;
    6340 var later = function() {
    6350 previous = new Date;
    6360 timeout = null;
    6370 result = func.apply(context, args);
    638 };
    6390 return function() {
    6400 var now = new Date;
    6410 var remaining = wait - (now - previous);
    6420 context = this;
    6430 args = arguments;
    6440 if (remaining <= 0) {
    6450 clearTimeout(timeout);
    6460 timeout = null;
    6470 previous = now;
    6480 result = func.apply(context, args);
    6490 } else if (!timeout) {
    6500 timeout = setTimeout(later, remaining);
    651 }
    6520 return result;
    653 };
    654 };

    656 // Returns a function, that, as long as it continues to be invoked, will not
    657 // be triggered. The function will be called after it stops being called for
    658 // N milliseconds. If `immediate` is passed, trigger the function on the
    659 // leading edge, instead of the trailing.
    6601 _.debounce = function(func, wait, immediate) {
    6610 var timeout, result;
    6620 return function() {
    6630 var context = this, args = arguments;
    6640 var later = function() {
    6650 timeout = null;
    6660 if (!immediate) result = func.apply(context, args);
    667 };
    6680 var callNow = immediate && !timeout;
    6690 clearTimeout(timeout);
    6700 timeout = setTimeout(later, wait);
    6710 if (callNow) result = func.apply(context, args);
    6720 return result;
    673 };
    674 };

    824 // Internal recursive comparison function for `isEqual`.
    8251 var eq = function(a, b, aStack, bStack) {
    826 // Identical objects are equal. `0 === -0`, but they aren't identical.
    827 // See the Harmony `egal` proposal: http://wiki.ecmascript.org/doku.php?id=harmony:egal.
    8280 if (a === b) return a !== 0 || 1 / a == 1 / b;
    829 // A strict comparison is necessary because `null == undefined`.
    8300 if (a == null || b == null) return a === b;
    831 // Unwrap any wrapped objects.
    8320 if (a instanceof _) a = a._wrapped;
    8330 if (b instanceof _) b = b._wrapped;
    834 // Compare `[[Class]]` names.
    8350 var className = toString.call(a);
    8360 if (className != toString.call(b)) return false;
    8370 switch (className) {
    838 // Strings, numbers, dates, and booleans are compared by value.
    839 case '[object String]':
    840 // Primitives and their corresponding object wrappers are equivalent; thus, `"5"` is
    841 // equivalent to `new String("5")`.
    8420 return a == String(b);
    843 case '[object Number]':
    844 // `NaN`s are equivalent, but non-reflexive. An `egal` comparison is performed for
    845 // other numeric values.
    8460 return a != +a ? b != +b : (a == 0 ? 1 / a == 1 / b : a == +b);
    847 case '[object Date]':
    848 case '[object Boolean]':
    849 // Coerce dates and booleans to numeric primitive values. Dates are compared by their
    850 // millisecond representations. Note that invalid dates with millisecond representations
    851 // of `NaN` are not equivalent.
    8520 return +a == +b;
    853 // RegExps are compared by their source patterns and flags.
    854 case '[object RegExp]':
    8550 return a.source == b.source &&
    856 a.global == b.global &&
    857 a.multiline == b.multiline &&
    858 a.ignoreCase == b.ignoreCase;
    859 }
    8600 if (typeof a != 'object' || typeof b != 'object') return false;
    861 // Assume equality for cyclic structures. The algorithm for detecting cyclic
    862 // structures is adapted from ES 5.1 section 15.12.3, abstract operation `JO`.
    8630 var length = aStack.length;
    8640 while (length--) {
    865 // Linear search. Performance is inversely proportional to the number of
    866 // unique nested structures.
    8670 if (aStack[length] == a) return bStack[length] == b;
    868 }
    869 // Add the first object to the stack of traversed objects.
    8700 aStack.push(a);
    8710 bStack.push(b);
    8720 var size = 0, result = true;
    873 // Recursively compare objects and arrays.
    8740 if (className == '[object Array]') {
    875 // Compare array lengths to determine if a deep comparison is necessary.
    8760 size = a.length;
    8770 result = size == b.length;
    8780 if (result) {
    879 // Deep compare the contents, ignoring non-numeric properties.
    8800 while (size--) {
    8810 if (!(result = eq(a[size], b[size], aStack, bStack))) break;
    882 }
    883 }
    884 } else {
    885 // Objects with different constructors are not equivalent, but `Object`s
    886 // from different frames are.
    8870 var aCtor = a.constructor, bCtor = b.constructor;
    8880 if (aCtor !== bCtor && !(_.isFunction(aCtor) && (aCtor instanceof aCtor) &&
    889 _.isFunction(bCtor) && (bCtor instanceof bCtor))) {
    8900 return false;
    891 }
    892 // Deep compare objects.
    8930 for (var key in a) {
    8940 if (_.has(a, key)) {
    895 // Count the expected number of properties.
    8960 size++;
    897 // Deep compare each member.
    8980 if (!(result = _.has(b, key) && eq(a[key], b[key], aStack, bStack))) break;
    899 }
    900 }
    901 // Ensure that both objects contain the same number of properties.
    9020 if (result) {
    9030 for (key in b) {
    9040 if (_.has(b, key) && !(size--)) break;
    905 }
    9060 result = !size;
    907 }
    908 }
    909 // Remove the first object from the stack of traversed objects.
    9100 aStack.pop();
    9110 bStack.pop();
    9120 return result;
    913 };

    468 }
    4690 else this._state = TEXT;
    4701 } else if(this._state === AFTER_STYLE_4){
    4711 if(c === ">" || whitespace(c)){
    4721 this._state = IN_CLOSING_TAG_NAME;
    4731 this._sectionStart = this._index - 5;
    4741 continue; //reconsume the token
    475 }
    4760 else this._state = TEXT;
    477 }
    478
    479
    480 else {
    4810 this._cbs.onerror(Error("unknown state"), this._state);
    482 }
    483
    484938396 this._index++;
    485 }
    486
    487 //cleanup
    4889406 if(this._sectionStart === -1){
    4890 this._buffer = "";
    4900 this._index = 0;
    491 } else {
    4929410 if(this._state === TEXT){
    4939411 if(this._sectionStart !== this._index){
    4941 this._cbs.ontext(this._buffer.substr(this._sectionStart));
    495 }
    4969414 this._buffer = "";
    4979415 this._index = 0;
    4980 } else if(this._sectionStart === this._index){
    499 //the section just started
    5000 this._buffer = "";
    5010 this._index = 0;
    5020 } else if(this._sectionStart > 0){
    503 //remove everything unnecessary
    5040 this._buffer = this._buffer.substr(this._sectionStart);
    5050 this._index -= this._sectionStart;
    506 }
    507
    5089426 this._sectionStart = 0;
    509 }
    510};
    511
    5121Tokenizer.prototype.pause = function(){
    5130 this._running = false;
    514};
    5151Tokenizer.prototype.resume = function(){
    5160 this._running = true;
    517};
    518
    5191Tokenizer.prototype.end = function(chunk){
    5209438 if(chunk) this.write(chunk);
    521
    522 //if there is remaining data, emit it in a reasonable way
    5239441 if(this._sectionStart > this._index){
    5240 var data = this._buffer.substr(this._sectionStart);
    525
    5260 if(this._state === IN_CDATA || this._state === AFTER_CDATA_1 || this._state === AFTER_CDATA_2){
    5270 this._cbs.oncdata(data);
    5280 } else if(this._state === IN_COMMENT || this._state === AFTER_COMMENT_1 || this._state === AFTER_COMMENT_2){
    5290 this._cbs.oncomment(data);
    5300 } else if(this._state === IN_TAG_NAME){
    5310 this._cbs.onopentagname(data);
    5320 } else if(this._state === IN_CLOSING_TAG_NAME){
    5330 this._cbs.onclosetag(data);
    534 } else {
    5350 this._cbs.ontext(data);
    536 }
    537 }
    538
    5399457 this._cbs.onend();
    540};
    541
    5421Tokenizer.prototype.reset = function(){
    5430 Tokenizer.call(this, this._options, this._cbs);
    544};

    5461Tokenizer.prototype._emitToken = function(name){
    547116067 this._cbs[name](this._buffer.substring(this._sectionStart, this._index));
    548116079 this._sectionStart = -1;
    549};
    550
    5511Tokenizer.prototype._emitIfToken = function(name){
    552116129 if(this._index > this._sectionStart){
    55339847 this._cbs[name](this._buffer.substring(this._sectionStart, this._index));
    554 }
    555116165 this._sectionStart = -1;
    556};
